function add_yearmonth(df::DataFrame)
    return hcat(df, :ym => col -> string((col(:dt) .|> Dates.format .=> "yyyy-mm") .|> String .|> x -> parse(Int, x)[1:6]) )
end
```

This function assumes that the `dt` column is of type `DateTime` and it extracts the year and month components from each DateTime in the column using `Dates.format` with a custom format string to ensure they are formatted as "yyyy-mm". It then converts each element of this new vector to an integer by parsing the string representation, taking only the first 6 characters (since "yyyy-mm" is exactly 6 characters long), and finally concatenates them together in the desired format `"yyyymm"` before appending the new column to the DataFrame.
